---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Breadcrumb from "../components/Breadcrumb.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Trust & Privacy"
  description="Trust boundary summary for skill7.dev: public marketplace pages stay public, while hosted product access for Sift uses account-based browser auth."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <Breadcrumb items={[
      { label: "Home", href: "/" },
      { label: "Marketplace", href: "/marketplace" },
      { label: "Trust & Privacy" },
    ]} />

    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="font-heading font-bold tracking-tight text-dark-hi">Trust &amp; Privacy</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-dark-lo">
        skill7.dev now has two different UX models, and they should not be mixed: public plugin install docs, and hosted product access for Sift.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="card-sm">
        <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-acid">Marketplace</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 font-heading text-2xl font-semibold text-dark-hi">Public by default</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-dark-lo">
          Marketplace pages are public catalog pages. They show install commands and plugin metadata. Browsing the catalog does not require a hosted account.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card-sm">
        <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-cyan">Sift</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 font-heading text-2xl font-semibold text-dark-hi">Account-based browser access</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-dark-lo">
          Sift uses browser auth on skill7.dev via Zitadel. That access flow is intentionally separate from plugin marketplace registration and install commands.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card-sm lg:col-span-2">
        <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-acid">Design rule</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-dark-lo">
          If something is a hosted product, it gets its own page and its own auth boundary. If something is a plugin, it stays in the marketplace and keeps the lowest-friction possible install path.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
